cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with video action recognition using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on creating human-understandable visual explanations suggests a focus on interpretability and explainability, which are also common themes in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of 3D convolutions and the exploration of network structures suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of natural language processing datasets (EPIC-Kitchens and EGTEA Gaze+) suggests a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
